  "prompt": "How much is unemployment in Texas?",
  "response": "As of 2023, the maximum weekly unemployment benefit amount in Texas is $563. However, the actual amount you receive depends on your previous earnings. The state calculates benefits based on your wages during the highest-paid quarter of your base period, typically ranging from $66 to $563 per week. To be eligible, you must meet certain work and wage requirements, and benefits are typically paid for up to 26 weeks.",
